{"id":164,"parent_id":108,"book_id":71,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":164,"title":"Making a Survival Kit","subtitle":"","short_title":"Making a Survival Kit","uri":"/manual/family-home-evening-resource-book/family-activities/making-a-survival-kit","content":[["div",{"id":"head57","uri":"/manual/family-home-evening-resource-book/family-activities/making-a-survival-kit.head57"},["h1","Making a Survival Kit"]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/manual/family-home-evening-resource-book/family-activities/making-a-survival-kit.p2"},"Outdoor activities are no fun when someone gets lost. Adequate preparation will usually keep this from happening, but some simple equipment can prepare a family member to survive if he does get lost. This activity will teach family members to make a lightweight survival kit that they can easily carry with them."],[".topic",["h2","Activity"],["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/family-home-evening-resource-book/family-activities/making-a-survival-kit.p4"},"First make sure that family members understand a few simple rules:"],["div",{"id":"f138","uri":"/manual/family-home-evening-resource-book/family-activities/making-a-survival-kit.f138"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],[".para","Wear a shrill whistle around your neck when you are hiking or fishing in an isolated area."]],["li",["span.label","2."],[".para","Tell someone where you are going and when you are coming back. Don’t leave the camping area by yourself."]],["li",["span.label","3."],[".para","Orient yourself to the area and do not explore longer or farther away than your family feels is safe."]],["li",["span.label","4."],[".para","Remember when you are lost to—"],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Keep calm, find a sheltered place, and stay put. Get out into the open if planes are overhead."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Build a fire if possible, conserve your heat and energy."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Mark your location. Move out from it to seek familiar landmarks and return to it."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Shout, use a whistle, and concentrate on being found—not on finding someone."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Prepare for the night, gather wood, build a shelter before dark."]]]]]],["div",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/family-home-evening-resource-book/family-activities/making-a-survival-kit.p14"},"Then have all family members help construct a survival kit. Make sure they know how to use each item. The following items can be put in a 2 1/2-by-4 1/2-by-16 1/2-inch (6-by-11-by-16-cm) leather pouch and will weigh less than one pound (.5 kilograms)."],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",{"colspan":"2","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["b","Survival Kit"]]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["b","Item"]]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["b","Uses"]]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Pocket knife with cutting blade, can opener, leather punch"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Carving, cutting, spearhead"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Metal canister 1 1/2-by-3 1/2-by-4 1/2 inches (4-by-9-by-11-cm). Many of the following items can be put in this canister."]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Cooking pan, reflector, cup"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Surgical tubing, 40 inches (100 cm)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Drinking tube, tourniquet, flipper"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","100 halazone tablets"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Water purification"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Six small cotton balls"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Swabs, pad, dressing"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1/32-inch (5-mm) twine, 96 inches (30 meters)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Fishing line, snare, sewing"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Aluminum foil, 12-by-18 inches (30-by-45 cm)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Cooking, heat reflector"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Wire survival saw 15 inches (36 cm)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Sawing"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Three razor blades"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Cutting, snares"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Twelve safety pins, 1 inch (1.5 cm)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Repairs, clothespins, securing shelter to rope"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Six No. 12 fish hooks and 12 feet (3.5 meters) of line"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Fishing, snares"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Three balls of steel wool"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Tinder for fire in wet weather"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Waterproof matches, candle, metal match"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Fire"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Metal whistle"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Signal, reflector"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Small sharpening stone"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Striking matches, sharpening"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Pencil and paper"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Leaving notes or directions"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Twelve heat tablets"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Cooking"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Electrician’s tape, 120 inches (3.6 meters) (wrapped around canister)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Repairs, fastening shelter to rope"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Six small band-aids"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","First aid"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Card showing ground-air signals"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Giving directions, sending distress signals, signaling location"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Six bouillon cubes, dried soups"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Food, morale, body heat"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Two plastic sheets 9-by-12-feet (2.6-by-3.6 meters)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Shelter, ground cloth, water collection"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1/8-inch (2-cm) nylon cord, 12 feet (3.5 meters)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Shelter rope, snares"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Sewing kits: two needles, three buttons, 6 feet of thread (1.8 meters)"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Patches, first aid"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Small compass with mirror on back"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Directions, signaling"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Additional Activities"],["div",{"id":"p69","uri":"/manual/family-home-evening-resource-book/family-activities/making-a-survival-kit.p69"},"Try each component in your backyard or on a simulated exercise to prepare yourself and your family for possible use."]]]],"refs":null}
